Ford GoBike Analysis¶

by Omar Ahmad Abdalaziz Aly¶

Investigation Overview¶

This investigation is conducted on the Ford GoBike dataset. The goal of this investigation is to reveal the relationship between variables and how they influence the duration of a bike trip¶

Dataset Overview¶

This data set includes information about individual rides made in a bike-sharing system covering the greater San Francisco Bay area.¶

binsize = 1
bins = np.arange(0, df_goBike['duration_min'].max()+binsize, binsize)
plt.figure(figsize=[15, 5])
plt.hist(data = df_goBike, x = 'duration_min', bins = bins)
plt.xlabel('Duration (Minutes)')
plt.xlim(0,130)
plt.title('Distribution of Duration in Minutes')
plt.show()

What is the day with most frequent trips?¶

Thursday seems to be the day with the most trips over all, while sunday and saturday seem to be the ones with the least trips¶

In [4]:
#function for labeling plots
def xytitle(xaxis,yaxis,title):
    plt.xlabel(xaxis)
    plt.ylabel(yaxis)    
    plt.title(title)
# The day of the week with the most trips made
base_color = sb.color_palette()[0]
plt.figure(figsize=[10,8])
sb.countplot(data = df_goBike, x = 'start_day', color = base_color, order = df_goBike['start_day'].value_counts().index);
xytitle('Day of Week','Count','Frequency of Trips per day')

Do days influence the duration of the trip?¶

No, days seem to have slight to no effect on the duration of the trip they all follow an almost identical distribution¶

In [5]:
# Does the day of the trip have an influence of duration?
plt.figure(figsize=[20,14])
sb.violinplot(data = df_goBike.query("duration_min<=30"),x = 'start_day',y='duration_min',color = base_color)
xytitle('Day of the Week','Duration (Minutes)','Duration per trip based on the day of the week')

How does user type influence the duration of the trip?¶

Subscribers are most likely to spend a longer period of time during a trip than customers¶
